  "body": "https://medium.com/metamask/breaking-changes-to-the-metamask-inpage-provider-b4dde069dd0a\n\n\n1) In Metamask, the provider by default has an empty array of accounts, which will be populated if the user gives access to the dapp, while Status' provider returns null. This causes Status to raise this error: \"The requested account has not been authorized by the user.\" in this code block \n\nIt is causing problems in Embark because it uses getAccounts a lot to determine if a dapp is connected or not.\n\n2) web3.eth.getCoinbase() returns default account , should return selected account for dapps",
