    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Are we removing the EIP1102 browser tool tip as part of this issue now?\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15470435/70454628-be572000-1a78-11ea-8433-27143ad5a6e3.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nTo recap the discussion from Discord:\r\n- By now, modern DApps are compliant with EIP1102. \r\n- And in fact, no longer work if privacy mode is disabled. Thus, the `Always allow` option will break up-to-date DApps.\r\n- As such, we will hide this tooltip to encourage the use of privacy mode in the browser. Users can disable privacy mode from their profile settings. Copy update TK.\r\n\r\nMore problematically, there is a lack of consistency between MM's implementation, Trust's, etc. DApps are almost guaranteed to be broken in some browsers now. We will touch base with MM to see how we can work together on improving this. ",
